values:
I finally convinced someone to play Skate with me.

Then Lawrence knocked over my xbox and the game now has a huge scratch on it and is unplayable.

I honestly, totally unironically, 100% seriouspost almost broke down and cried.

I finally saw Shai Hulud tonight. They played a bunch of amazing songs.

Matt Fox shook my hand and thanked me personally for singing along.

It was awesome.

Was just looking at my last entry's comments and, yes Kym, I forgot to talk about our bathroom painting adventure! For those who did not join us on this adventure, I happen to have a bathroom inside my room. It has a shower in it, but I used it to store transformers rather than wash myself. Here is a picture of it before painting (shower emptied out): It's tough to take a picture of such a small room. As you can see it looks like crap. So we took a day off from slacking off and painted it! I actually was supposed to paint it LAST summer but I'm glad I waited because I got help that way. Thanks Kym! Other unfinished business from last entry: My mom is back from Florida. So far she has not tried to shoot mind bullets at me, so I think we're ok. She's moving her dance teaching business out of this rented place and into a much better, cheaper place (on top of the future shop downtown), and she's trying to get a website for it. I tried to help but it's very confusing. Also me and Lawrence DID go to Q-town for that show, it was pretty great. Radical Attack SUCKED, whatever that other band that shared half their members with Radical Attack was SUCKED, If Hope Dies was alright, Walls of Jericho was alright (some douchebag pushed the singer off the stage and she just left and they stopped their set), All That Remains WASN'T THERE AGAIN (I've paid 3 times to see these guys and they only showed up once), A Life Once Lost was alright except the people there didn't seem to enjoy them and they actually got really mad at us, The Red Chord was missing a member but still destroyed everything in sight (they'd just come back from a tour with the Hulud so that's like, +20 respect points right there), and Unearth finished up with a killer set! Ken threw a speaker at us!!! O: Then I got a guitar pick from him: In conclusion a lot of the people at that show were retarded and didn't know how to dance and had no taste in music and I deeply hate them all. Otherwise had a great time. We were also supposed to go to NYC for Ozzfest but we didn't because I was totally broke. I am still partially broke, but I worked a bit so I got SOME money. First I sold drugs for the Gillett Entertainment Group: JAY KAY I ACTUALLY PUSHED BOXES. It was the Elvis Story take out. Helllooo 45 dollars an hour! Then I did take in/out for the vans warped tour, that was fun. I went to bed after the take in but I came back a bit early to try to catch some bands, saw Everytime I Die and Alexisonfire, totally missed HORSE the Band and Protest the Hero (more on PTH later). Then we took down the half-pipe and the guy there (who was clearly high!!! FUCKING KIDS) was like "thanks guys each of you please take a case of this" so I took home a case of this "...lost" energy drink, it's ok. Tastes like free (and orange). Fucking hippy didn't want to get the case back on the truck! And then later that week I did Mariah Carey, that was also cool. I saw Sean Paul and his official rum bottle carrying guy. It's kind of tough to remember what I've done all summer. I haven't updated since the beginning of June! Oh yeah, at the beginning of July was the CUMC!!! I don't know if I've mentioned this in here before, but it's a math conference, this year it was hosted by my university. Next year it's going to be SFU (in Vancouver) and I am going also! yaaaaaay! Anyway it was cool I learned a bunch of things and of course I suck at talking to people and I didn't actually make any friends until the closing banquet which, for some reason, was on an island somewhere. Turns out these people had been refering to me as "emo kid" all week. Motherfuckers. Then I showed them I was cool and then it was totally cool. Cool. I've been reading (math and non-math) books during the summer (...the library has AC, my house doesn't) and that combined with the conference has me actually pretty excited to go back to school in a couple of days (sept. 5). It's weird, honestly, I don't think I've ever felt that way. I have a nice schedule next semester too, I'm happy with it. Ok I'm pretty much out of "big things I did this summer". Today I went to HMV and bought PTH's Kezia and Misery Signals' new record, Mirrors. Haven't listened to Mirrors yet, but jesus christ Protest the Hero is great! I'd downloaded a couple of their songs a little while back after seeing the video for their first single off of Kezia (Blindfolds Aside), and all the other songs I got kind of sucked. Turns out they were all old songs, and they actually refuse to play them live because they suck so bad. So I downloaded more songs off the last record and was quite satisfied! Truth is I am totally gay for concept albums, and I have been looking for something to listen to ever since I got tired of listening to Co&Ca's blahblahblah Burning Star IV volume fuck off claudio. I'm glad this CD never goes into crazy 20 minute keyboard solos (not that Co&Ca does, but I've listened to way too much DT and Ayreon), and has good, non-cheesy lyrics. Well ok, there's the bit in Bury the Hatchet that goes "I SWEAR I HAVE COMPASSION, I'VE JUST BEEN TRAINED TO DISREGARD THE PRISONER'S LIFE, 'CAUSE I'M THE PRISOOOOOOON GUUUUUUAAAAAAAAAARD" which sounds exactly like something Arjen Lucassen would write (I'd wield my blade with crimson gusto for I'm the proud barbarian host!). Also no wonder Wikipedia lists Between the Buried and Me as one of PTH's influences, the intro for Turn Soonest to the Sea sounds EXACTLY like the intro to Alaska! Tomorrow Kym's comin' over and we are eating motherfucking chicken tacos. FUCK YEAH. Then I think friday we are going to that science center thing and it sounds pretty cool. I'm pretty big on science! Hopefully they don't make mistakes or oversimplifications because I'm also pretty big on being a jerk about it. I suck.

Let me just start by telling everyone to shut up, I don't give a fuck if I haven't updated in 3 whole months >: ( School is over. About time. Don't yet have all my grades, but so far they're like B+/B-. Hoping for an A on the one I don't have yet. Overall it's half-decent I guess, but I'm pretty certain I'm getting out of Honours. I don't really like it and I'm not even sure I fit the requirements anymore. I have to go ask someone I guess. For now I'm just gonna sit around for a few more days I guess, then I suppose I should look for some kind of job. If anybody's wondering what I've been doing during the past 3 months, I don't even remember what I did last week. I went to some meets, played some video games, probably saw a movie or two, I think I was sick at some point, hung out with friends on various occasions and drank various amounts of various things, with varying success. I am currently in the process of going through all the tony hawk games (except the first one, I don't have that one) again for some reason. I'm not sure why. The other day I went to Kym's house and we ate some kind of taco thing, except it was baked and flat, and I don't know why they even call it taco bake because it doesn't really have anything to do with tacos, but it was pretty damn good. And yes I know I talked about tacos in my last entry, but that was like 3 fucking months ago. I eat things other than tacos, I swear. Anyway, we also played video games, finished SH2. The "leave" ending sucks. Then eventually we were woken up by the horrible sound of jackhammering (and not the good kind). At least it was really nice out and such. Eventually I left and, on the bus, some loser nerd had written the integration by parts formula (the indefinite version) on the back of the seat in front of me. I laughed, people stared. Yesterday I decided I would try to clean up this damn house. It's a start, I guess. Yeah, you'd think having like 20 cats in the house would help with the cleaning, but you'd be so horribly wrong. Those furry little poopmachines wouldn't even bother picking up a broom to save their lives. Fucking deadbeat potheads. One of them had kids like a month ago. My parents call her "little mom" because, well, she keeps fucking getting babies. So now there's two new tiny grey furballs running around. I think you have to wait something like 2 months before we can get rid of them. We are getting rid of all the cats except my grumpy old Harold (who almost never leaves his corner now because the mom keeps trying to murder him in his sleep for no god damn reason), and the three remaining kids from the mom's last batch: Scarlett, David (his actual name is Charles, what the fuck kind of stupid ass name is that?) and Internet (real name is Babette, which is lame as well). The Internet just had babies too, but we're pretty sure they didn't survive. Scarlett's looking kinda fat too. The ones we are keeping are all getting fixed of course (Harold has been for a long time). This should have been done years ago. Also on the list of things that need to be done: half the phones haven't worked for the past like 6 months, my window has been fucked for over a year, and the window upstairs has been broken for 6 years. In other news: Yeah, I have no life. I wanted to skate today but it's raining so I guess it ain't happenin. Maybe I'll do more cleaning, I dunno. Also I got a haircut. Finally. Tomorrow I'm hanging out with Kym! I don't know what exactly we'll be doing, but then again I never really do. Hell, I don't even know what I'm doing right now. ...and it breaks my heeeeart, like dancin up all niiight ride so hiiigh, we both start thinking bout another woooorld, toniiiight and it feels so wrooooong LIKE NOTHING WE'VE EVER, FELT BEFOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOORE

I haven't updated in almost a month and I had so many things to write about but I forgot now. Here I had something to say about ketchup chips but I can't find my dad's camera so forget it. School is going okay I guess. Had a midterm friday, didn't go so well, whatever. Trying to keep up with assignments and everything, working okay. Have 2 more midterms before the study break, then another one after. Very exciting. The other day my anal teacher thought my name was Patrick. I was offended. Those two newbies that were at the last goonmeet don't remember who I am either. But that's alright, I remember you guys, and I don't like you. So, you know, fuck off. Friday night this week I hung out with Kym! I bought a book. That's right, I can read. It was recommended in that one thread about the spy emails and I thought it looked interesting and it was written by that guy who wrote a book about Fermat's Last Theorem that monsieur Darmon suggested and I want to buy too (along with a book about Galois theory I think but I forget now). I haven't really started reading it, will try tonight. Anyone else pissed off that Fermat's Little Theorem and Last Theorem have the same acronym? Same goes for uniformly continuous, uniformly Cauchy and uniformly convergent. Why do all the uniforms have to start with a c? Fuck this shit. Also I just name-dropped 4 french mathematicians, take that you losers. Ok back to friday night, then we went for bubble tea which was pretty sweet but I had trouble sucking those balls because my straw was too small. THEN we went to Pho Thahn Long or however that is spelled and after that we went to PUB. PUB actually has a name but it also has a giant sign that just says PUB so we call it PUB. It was really empty but they had a disco ball and nobody was dancing and it was sad. It was cool, I had fun. Last night Lawrence came over because our camera appears to be working so we decided to try to work on some things. It was pretty cool. Then after he left I went for a walk! It was like 1AM. I saw Allopatrick on the street, he was walking alone too. I was like wtf. He probably doesn't remember who I am either, but at least he doesn't think my name is Patrick because that is his own name and you'd think you'd remember people who have the same name as you. When I walked back home, I walked by PUB at like 2:20ish, and there were like 5 people dancing on the dance floor under the disco ball. Various minds were blown. A little while back I went to a show with Kym, it was pretty good. Adair, FFTL and SOTY all pretty much suck, but they sounded better live and it was enjoyable. ETID was awesome of course but it was too short. They played Pretty Dirty! I was so happy. They still didn't play Tusk and Temper, that song is so good. Also, The Logic of Crocodiles is the last pre-Hot Damn! song they still played. And now they didn't play it this time. The new single is The New Black. You guys don't understand what this means! It's only going to get worse from here on out :( DAMN YOU KEITH! They did play a lot of good songs though. If I remember correctly: Apocalypse Now and Then, Keith the Music, Bored Stiff, Easy Tiger, Pretty Dirty, maybe Champing at the Bit (not sure) from GP, and then Off Broadway, I Been Gone a Long Time, Floater, Godspeed Us to Sea and Ebolarama from HD! Anyway, it was great. Seeing them again at the beginning of march with the awesome lineup of Haste the Day, Bleeding Through and Between the Buried and Me. As of now I am still going alone but oh well. A lot of the really good shows I've been to I went by myself. A couple of weeks ago, I forget why, my friends and I decided to go out and eat tacos. Then Blakkie was too poor because she bought new glasses, so we decided to make tacos instead. Then somehow it came to be that that night would be Tacofest 2006. So we bought stuff to make tacos, mexican beer, downloaded mexican music, and I busted out the sombrero. I don't know why I'm so obsessed with Mexico, honestly. First these are the aforementioned new glasses she bought. What the christ. Here is the vegetable master hard at work. Always whining about the shitty vegetables they have at my food store. Screw you man >: ( This is my :ese: impression. It is not very good and I look vaguely retarded. When I was cooking the meat I guess I messed up because it exploded on Ben's shirt And so then I lended him my limp bizkit t-shirt. He still has it, mofucker >: ( I love this picture because it is pretty much the worst picture of all time. Then I guess it was siesta time! Blakkie brought this picture of us at prom. Here are some people holding it up Here is a close-up: You may have noticed a black guy in the corner who none of us really know. He's just chilling in our picture and looking really confused as to what the hell he's doing there. Well Johnny, I'd like to know what the hell you're doing there too. I guess I don't really have anything else to talk about. Can't wait until spring break! I swear winter is like already over, it's not coming back this time. I want to skateboard again soon, winter blows. Damnit now it's 6, I'm hungry.

Holy jesus fuck my knees hurt. I am leaving in like 2 minutes to go see my grandpa, and I'm pretty sure I'm still drunk. I'm also not exactly sure why I'm posting.

HAPPY NEW YEAR MOTHERBITHCES

edit: i left my bedroom door open (which i never do) while i wrote this and SOMEONE puked on my carpet...THREE TIMES. i'm pretty sure it wasn't me, either. fuck this year.

Today is my birthday. Half of my presents are in the mail somewhere I think, but that's alright, I'm used to it, that's what always happens. Me and my waiting until the last minute to tell people things I want. Saturday night I went to Kym's house for like dinner and stuff, it was pretty cool. I haven't really eaten turkey in a long time but that was really good. Then I got some sweet-ass gifts! I am currently still wearing this math-related t-shirt that says "i am not real" on it (explanation). I got it from her along with some awesome SA emoticon stickers (not pictured) and the :ese: and :rolleyes: pins: I am quite pleased. From my parents I got the black 30Gb video iPod I requested, with absolutely necessary Shai Hulud lyric engraved on the back: It's from This Song: For True and Passionate Lovers of Music, obviously. Yeah, there wasn't enough space for the, well, spaces. I also got the new HORSE the Band CD, which I haven't really had time to listen to yet. It does have a song about Birdo and mad keyboard breakdowns so, I mean, what could go wrong? Last night we did kind of the reverse of saturday, it was fun. My dad bit into one of those tiny tomatoes and it exploded all over Kym's face. She had tomato in her hair and everything, it was pretty fucking funny. Today I am making a cake for my birthday with my mom. It's in the oven right now. My mom doesn't cook either, I hope we didn't fuck it up. Jesus, I haven't written in so long that I don't know what to write about at all. Exams sucked. I totally fucked up anal and I ended up with a C+. But it's over now...until january 3rd. What the fuck. I have never started so early, this is retarded. I have to meet with an advisor pretty soon, too, because I'm not quite sure what I should do at this point since I really didn't do very well anally. Oh well. I bought some pants the other day. Girls' jeans. That's right. Ben wasn't manly enough to try some on, what a loser. I tried to take pictures the other day but it didn't work so good: They look great I swear. Ok, I guess I have some kind of show-mentioning quota for every post, so here we go: Every Time I Die on january 25th AND march 6th with From First to Last/Story of the Year (which aren't very good) and Bleeding Through/Haste The Day/Between the MOTHERFUCKING Buried and Me (which are fucking brutal and amazing), respectively. Also maybe Taste of Chaos (april 15th) which is apparently completely different this year, as As I Lay Dying will be present, among other weird choices, like Deftones, Dredg (LOOK I AM SINGING THROUGH A TRUMPET) and Pelican. Oh, and Atreyu, but that's not as weird. Last year it was like...My Chemical Romance or something. They're not very chaotic, honestly. In conclusion, here are some pictures of my cats I guess: The other day, there was an almost full glass of water on my nightstand and a cat knocked it over and so my bed was flooded. I wanted to put my sheets in the dryer but...someone was having a nap. Yeah.

I JUST WANT TO JOIN THE PARTTYYYYYYYYYYY but the song on the karaoke says if you wanna celebrate compassion is cruelty and hip hip hooray! sup dudes. It is friday. Awesome. School sucks I am so tired. Also Marco you are a retard and I hate you and seriously go fuck yourself. hey guess what I went to a show the other day here are approximatively 20 pages about it Ok so we got there and it was pretty empty and I was like wtf what's going on! Then mewithoutyou played they were alright they were just chillin you know. The singer/hobo doing the vocals had a cool story about how he used to date this girl who lived here and I don't think he ever finished the story. I liked when they started taking apart the drumkit while the over-expressive drummer was still drummin'. All in all pretty sweet. Then Dredg. I don't remember what the music was like, all I can think of is the guy's stupid voice he sounded like he was in a god damn greek power metal band. I had to listen to a lot of greek music this summer and god damnit he sounded exactly like that and no sir I don't like it. Then he sang through a trumpet. Yeah that's right, he didn't play it, he sang through it. Then they did the same taking-away-pieces-of-the-drumkit-while-still-playing thing and I was like who the fuck do you think you are?! Oh I got lost in the bathroom. It was really confusing. Like I saw this guy peeing at the other end of the room and I walked forward towards what I thought was the exit and there were only more urinals there and THE SAME GUY WAS PEEING THERE. What the christ. I made it eventually (I think). THE BLOOD BROTHERS! There are not enough dual-screaming bands these days, seriously. I mean it's all like "oh this guy does clean vocals, and this guy screams", and I mean that's okay I guess but come on! It was so good, those dudes have some really nice screams. I don't remember exactly what songs they played, there was Feed Me To The Forest, Love Rhymes With Hideous Car Wreck (I did the little handclap at the beginning I felt so cool), Peacock Skeleton With Crooked Feathers (sooooo good), Rats and Rats and Rats for Candy, Crimes, Live At The Apocalypse Cabaret...that's all I remember. No Celebrator and no Devastator either >: ( Then Coheed killed of course. They had like background stuff! There were like drawings of the Writer, Erica and Ten Speed...and a giant fucking guillotine (not a drawing)! It opened its wings at some time throughout the set, it was sweet. Setlist: Keeping The Blade Always And Never Welcome Home Ten Speed (Of God's Blood And Burial) Delirium Trigger Blood Red Summer Apollo I: The Writing Writer The Ring In Return Once Upon Your Dead Body A Favor House Atlantic Three Evils (Embodied in Love and Shadow) Wake Up The Suffering Devil In Jersey City Everything Evil Encore: In Keeping Secrets of Silent Earth: 3 The Willing Well IV: The Final Cut It was really fucking awesome. Finally got to find out what the hell the 12-string neck on that doubleneck guitar is for. Claudio uses this guitar it in the Welcome Home video for no apparent reason (because he doesn't play the second neck in it), but now we saw him use it for Always And Never, right before Welcome Home. Anyway, pretty much all fucking awesome songs, except for Wake Up which I just can't stand. Claudio said on the DVD that they were going to play The Light and the Glass! What is this bullshit! There is no way anyone likes Wake Up more than L&G. NO WAY. I'm also a little sad that there was nothing from The Velourium Camper (especially part 1 or 2), and no Willing Well I or II. I guess playing WWIII after Apollo I would have been retarded since they are essentially the same song (at a different pace, with a different ending), but I would have prefered WWIII instead. There was also no Cuts Marked In The March of Men, and no The Crowing (wtf, they've been playing this one like every show for along time). Also, they played a super extended version of WWIV which was pretty good at first but it got a little old and I was pretty tired by then. Travis always looks pissed but when he did his solo and he had that tube thing in his mouth he looked happy, I thought it was pretty funny. He was all WAAAAAAAAHwahwaawhahwhWAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH Also, Claudio's singing is much much better now. Or at least his breathing is, I don't remember him being out of breath at all, unlike what I'd seen in all their live videos. And then at the end...the guillotine blade dropped! It was pretty sweet I guess. I'm really fucking hungry. oh god what will i do

I haven't updated in like...3 weeks. I've been busy I guess. Lots of crap to do for school. I actually managed to do my work BEFORE supper today and then when I was done eating I was all confused and I didn't know what to do. I cleaned my room! Then I thought I'd update I guess. So this is it. I just realized I bought a shitload of crap this past week or so. I bought some sweet tix: The AILD/Unearth/Slipknot show was sold out. Then I realized it wasn't really worth it anyway, because I really don't want to see those clowns again (Slipknot, I mean). I also bought We <3 Katamari which is so fucking awesome (more awesome than the first) that I constantly cream my pants and wonder what it would be like to then roll up these pants AND MAKE A FUCKIGN STAR OUT OF THEM Oh those japanese, sooo zany. You can roll underwater! On fire! Roll up a fat guy so he gets fatter and beats this other sumo wrestler! Roll up planets in space to fukken ROLL UP THE SUN!!! You can also roll coop 2-player which sounds absolutely insane. Both players need to roll in the same direction to actually do anything. I had ordered Good Apollo, I'm Burning Star IV, Volume One: From Fear Through the Eyes of Madness, along with the graphic novel, and a fucking badass keywork belt buckle, from www.merchnow.com, and I got the package in the mail yesterday. Only there was no belt buckle. Just a note saying "oh sorry no more belt buckles". The thing is, they sold way more preorders of the comic book than they had in stock, so they ran out. So it took them forever to send me my stuff, as they didn't want to send part of it now and the rest later. But did they hold the belt buckle for me, which I paid for like a month ago, until they could ship my stuff? NO. Someone else bought it, and they ran out. What the shit is this? I mean they gave me back the money I paid for it, but I fucking paid for it! You're not making any more money from selling it to someone else, you fuckers! YOU ALREADY HAD MY MONEY! I am fairly certain it was a more or less limited edition thing and there will probably not be anymore, and I am pissed the fuck off. A lot of people got free shit because their orders took longer than expected, including an Equal Vision sampler CD (had songs by Fall of Troy, Bear vs Shark and Fear Before the March of Flames on it) and some stickers. I got nothing. I got less than I was supposed to get. I've bought for well over 100 bucks of t-shirts from fucking merchnow, and they've always been fine, but jesus christ this is fucking bullshit. It's like that fucking episode of Seinfeld, with the rental car: "Agent: Can I help you? Name please? Jerry: Seinfeld. I made a reservation for a mid-size, and she's a small. I'm kidding around, of course. Agent: Okay, let's see here. I'm sorry, we have no mid-size available at the moment. Jerry: I don't understand, I made a reservation, do you have my reservation? Agent: Yes, we do, unfortunately we ran out of cars. Jerry: But the reservation keeps the car here. That's why you have the reservation. Agent: I know why we have reservations. Jerry: I don't think you do. If you did, I'd have a car. See, you know how to take the reservation, you just don't know how to *hold* the reservation and that's really the most important part of the reservation, the holding. Anybody can just take them. *flails arms wildly in the air, pretending to write down reservations* Agent: Let me, uh, speak with my supervisor." FUCK YOU MERCHNOW Ok yeah now about the CD itself, it is pretty good, I haven't really had a chance to listen to it much. The only good thing about having gotten it form merchnow is that the canadian version doesn't have the awesome black sleeve thing. Alright, don't read the next paragraph if you have no idea what Coheed and Cambria is about or if you don't want to get really confused. I think Claudio has really gone mad now. A story within a story? A story about the writer of the story, but who is not actually the real Claudio Sanchez, but a character in his story, who writes the story inside this story? I didn't really mind when I realized that the Claudio character in the story within the story (not the real Claudio) was quite obviously a Jesus figure, and then that the "Writer" of this story was quite obviously God, but when I realized that about half of the story inside the story is really about the real Claudio and not just a space opera with some bibilical themes, I thought it was a bit weird. I mean, if it's not actually a story about space wars and badass cyborgs and wizards and shit, it's really just a guy singing about how this girl broke his heart...and he wants to murder her. When he said he accidentally wrote himself into the story, I just thought he'd named a character after himself, but it's really obvious now. I mean, Claudio has to leave Newo Ikkin to go save the world as The Crowing (or something like that), and the real Claudio had to leave Nikki Owens to...well I don't know, become a rockstar I guess. And then the Writer has Miss Erica Court, who he apparently used as the model for his Newo character. So really we have two (at least) different representations of the same cheating, lying whore of an ex-girlfriend. Way to let go of the past, Sanchez. Well, that's my interpretation anyway. I'm thinking he got sick of the actual story and was like "...okay how do I end this...oh I know, I'll write myself into the story AGAIN, writing the story that I wrote myself in, and then have a FUCKING DEMONIC TALKING BICYCLE talk me into killing off Ambellina so that The Crowing gets pissed and kills off all my characters." I mean it's a pretty cool unexpected twist to have the story inside the story, and I actually really like the story, but I enjoyed it more when it was about space and the keywork and the IRO-bots and all that crap instead of some writing dude. About the graphic novel, I thought it was really pretty, although kind of short and hard to follow. Also, it has a BUNCH of grammar/spelling errors for something with maybe 500 words total. Also, a lot of the characters look exactly the same. Here's some pictures: This is the FIRST PANNEL OF THE COMIC. It's supposed to be "its creator", by the way. Way to go editor guy! I think this is the Writer, but sometimes it's confusing. Welcome Home is a fucking rocking song though. Ten Speed, crazy-ass talking demon bicycle. ...yeeeeeeah Oh yeah, bought the Family Guy movie DVD too, haven't had time to watch it though. That "never before seen!" thing is a sticker. I think that's funny. Like, are they eventually going to not put the sticker on there anymore after a while? Are they going to change it to "you might have seen this before" or "dude buy my fucking movie, american dad is shit i just need some dough -seth mcfarlane"? Actually american dad is ok I guess. WHAT THE HELL IS THAT? * folding napkins* british metrosexual soccer icon david beckham, i can't do fricking swans! Yeah booboo enjoyed that one. Alright well I guess I'm going to go sleep now. I just realized this entry was pretty much ENTIRELY about shit I've bought. I don't really know what else to talk about, I'm always working on some assignments or something. The Analysis and Algebra ones are usually kind of hard but I really like doing it and I feel like I've learned something by the end, so it's ok. The rest isn't so bad, really. I'm really not liking having to do Cal 3 again (because they wouldn't credit my 201-EEE which is was pretty much the same thing), the teacher is so fucking slow. Like I have my 3 math classes in a row in the morning, and that one's the last, and the first two professors are pretty fast and are alternating between theorems and proofs constantly, and then I get this guy. He's like "so we have...this...theorem...now, I'm not going to...prove...this theorem...I don't...have time...I'm going to have to...hurry up"...every class. My Analysis teacher apologized for like 10 minutes once when he didn't prove a theorem. It never happened again. It's really not on the same level I guess. Now I'm worried that I'll keep going ah-ha! cal 3 is easy! and then do really bad at the end. It's not easy, it was my hardest class last semester. I'll be ok I guess. Oh, I found this note on the floor in that class the other day: I thought it was funny. Who the hell says "commence"? ...Is it creepy that I kept someone else's note? Oh geek metal, when have you failed me? Never, that's when. YET I MUST JOURNEY OOOOOOOOOON! OOOOOOOOOON AAAAAAAAND OOOOOOOOOOOOON! Well, this was actually a pretty good week, although I don't really know why. Monday was a wednesday, wednesday was a wednesday, and thursday I didn't have my Math class in the morning so I got THREE DAYS when I got to wake up later!!!! I suppose that helped. I had a bunch of exams though...and an oral on wednesday. It actually went pretty good! It was a team thing but the teacher said our presentation in general was excellent...I didn't do so well for my part (I was kind of shaking) so I guess it was at least good. I am so proud. But then thursday night I didn't sleep a lot and so I didn't feel so good friday during the day. I went to bed at 9...and woke up at noon saturday. Saturday night I was supposed to do something with Lawrence, Ben and Blakkie (we now spell it this way because of the second man from on the right in this picture) but Ben said he had to "study" (most likely meaning "talk to his girlfriend on the phone"...asshole) so he didn't come. And once again, we got started on doing things too late and the earliest we could go to the movies was 9:20, meaning it was 11:30 when we got out of the movies, and Blakkie had to leave. So then it was just me and Lawrence, again. We played some Megaman 2 and...5 I think. Then he left. ...I just realized I have not said one word about the show. It was not as good as last time, but it was pretty good. TBS is horrible, though. Oh god it was awful. But anyway, I got out of school at noon and so I sat around for an hour and then decided I would go see if there were any people there. There weren't. I went to eat and slowly walked back there...still no one. I walked around...trying to kill time. I really didn't want to be first in line. Apparently no one else does. At about 3, I walked by again and I saw three people standing there, including the security guy, so I went and stood by. The two guys in front of me were from Ottawa, and the security guy was like "...the doors open in like 4 hours, go walk around or something, since you're not from here"...so they left. And so...I was first in line, against my will. I talked with the security guy dude for a while, he was pretty nice. This guy wearing a suit and gloves and sunglasses came by later on and he was like "I need two tickets for my boss for [something]" and the security guy was like "Sorry, the box office is closed right now, but you can go buy tickets at [some other place like 5 minutes away]" and the suit guy said "No, that's too far. Listen, my boss knows the guy who owns this place, and I need these tickets for him or he will not be happy." but security guy really could no do anything about it and suit guy left eventually. He said to me something like "jesus, what the hell was up with that guy?" and I told him I thought he looked like Patrick Bateman and he actually knew what I was talking about! That was pretty cool. Then FINALLY someone came up and stood behind me in line. We started talking about the various bands playing and stuff, and then he was like "Man, it's like no one wanted to be first in line or something. I was walking around here and I saw these two girls and they were looking around and it seemed like they were there for the show but they left and went to do other things. I didn't want to be first in line either so I went to the Eaton centre and I saw them there! Oh and I saw you walking around here earlier too. I'm glad you broke the ice, though." and then I was like "yeah I was tricked into it ". Anyway, later on the two dudes from Ontario came back and we talked for a while, the four of us. I KIND OF MADE FRIENDS!!! I was so happy. Then we waited for hours. Last Atreyu show I went to, I stood in line next to a girl who was saving spots for her friends, and eventually one of them came by and so he stood like, almost in front of me (facing me) for a couple of hours. I saw him again monday, and he gave me a "where the fuck do I know you from?" look, even though I've never talked to him or anything. He looked really confused. We went inside eventually, and I was kind of disappointed because they had a barricade/trench thing, and those suck. Anyway, Funeral for a Friend was pretty good. Then Atreyu, which was great. They had the guy from FFAF come back to help do the last part of Lip Gloss and Black, that was pretty cool. Oh and the new bassist (not so new anymore, he was at the last show) is fucking awesome and breakdances while he plays. Then...TBS. I only kind of like ONE of their songs...and they didn't play it. Also, their singer apparently loves to twirl the mic around...and wraps the chord around his neck and stuff. Every couple of songs, one of the techs had to run out on stage to untangle that fucking mess, and he looked really pissed off. I thought it was hilarious. Oh, and maybe I'm getting old, but the music didn't really feel all that loud. The little girls screaming about how they wanted to marry TBS' singer are the only reason my ears were ringing after, I think. Oh god they were loud. The singer also said in between songs that he really liked our outfits. He was probably talking mainly about the people in front (because he could see them better) and so my outfit is now officially gay-approved! Hoooray! Anyway, even though that wasn't so great, it was worth it for the social interaction alone. I talked to people I didn't know!!! And...maybe I'm the only one who feels this way, but I think being in a large crowd at a show like this is like a giant, slightly violent group hug. I like it, despite the bruises. Better than being alone. Okay, maybe I'm crazy. I'm going to see Nightwish on december 16th...that should be pretty cool. Even more awesome, january 8th...UNEARTH! And Killswitch Engage! And...Slipknot. I don't really like Slipknot that much anymore, but it will still be fucking awesome. That's about it for this week...we finished doing the remastered version of MATS and started filming one of the other projects...I think it's too late for my DDR segment and unless we can wait until next summer, it will never get done. That sucks, it was going to be fucking awesome. HERE I AAAAAAM, AT THE CROOOOSSING OF LIIIFE, IIII STAAAAAAND, OOON MY OOOOOOWN, LOOKING DOOOOWN THEEEE ROOOOOAD! HEAR MY CRYYYY, AAAANSWER MEEEE!
